Thank you to the Growers. Thank you to the Movers. Thank you to the Hosters.
.
Movember 2019 may be over, but it won’t be forgotten. The dedication of all the Mo Bros and Mo Sistas around the world has raised vital funds and awareness that will help men live happier, healthier, longer lives. Thank you for helping change the face of men’s health.
.
.
#Movember #MensHealth #WhyIMo

It may be December, but the meMOries live on. Why not mark your Movember with a limited edition print of this ‘SCARY’ mural which was revived for Movember by artist, Ben Eine. It also doubles as an excellent festive gift.

Eine printed 60 Movember Mo’s as a wallpaper behind the lettering of one of London’s longest standing murals, to represent the number of men who die by suicide every hour, globally.

Get your hands on one of the 100 prints from ourtypes.com.
.
.
#Movember #MensHealth #Moustache #Graffiti #BenEine #mentalhealthawareness

You’ve raised funds, you’ve raised awareness, you’ve been an all-star Mo Bro/Mo Sista, and from the bottom of our hairy hearts we thank you. But don’t stop there. This GivingTuesday, go big for men’s health with Dares for Donations.
.
.
Set a target. Share your dare using #DaresForDonations. Let everyone know the lengths you’ll go to for men’s health. Commit to doing it on GivingTuesday when you hit your target, and call on your friends and family to help you get there. Capture it all on camera, post it, send it, share it far and wide – show everyone what men’s health means to you. Don’t forget to tag @movember.
.
.
#movember #GivingTuesday #WhyIMo #MensHealth
Missing your Mo? There is one option...

In the words of James Blunt “goodbye my lover, goodbye my friend, you have been the one, you have been the one for me.”
.
You brought a moustache into the world this Movember and saying goodbye to your hairy friend is never easy. Whatever you decide to grace your face with next, it's not too late to make a final push for donations.
.
.
#Movember #MensHealth #Moustache
However you’re closing out Movember, do it in style, with your crew - as our first 30 Mo Bros did.

“My father never showed any sadness, sometimes anger, but never sadness. I think I only ever saw him cry twice:  once at my grandma’s funeral and the last time we ever saw each other at Dublin airport. That’s one of the reasons that his suicide was so hard to take. How could this man, the happiest person I ever knew, feel so sad and alone that he felt he had no other choice?
.
.
What I wasn’t ready for was for life to continue at a regular pace. In the year after it happened, I spiraled pretty badly. I gained a lot of weight, I lost joy in a lot of things in life, I lost a relationship with a girl because I was depressed, angry, and drinking all the time. Some further poor choices culminated in me getting robbed at gunpoint and beaten to a pulp in my own home. I needed to take control of my life before it was too late. .
.
To this day, I still struggle with depression, anxiety, anger. I have dreams where my dad will show up, seemingly still alive, and then poof he's gone again. I contribute that to not really going out and getting the help I needed and not being honest with myself that I’m not okay. It’s taken me a long time to be ready to start the road to a recovery, or at the very least try to be in a better place than life has led me to so far. But I finally feel like I am ready.”- Alec Watson (Ottawa) .
.
Visit the link in profile to read Alec’s full story.
.
.
#WhyIMo #Movember #MentalHealthAwareness #MensHealth

The average man with a Mo touches it 760 times a day. How many times have you touched yours this month?

Today is also the day I realised that “your welcome” in Japanese is dou itashimashite and pronounced "don't touch my moustache"
What a time to learn that.
.
.
#Movember #Moustache #Facts

Have you achieved “the look” you were going for this Movember?
.
.
#Movember #Moustache #MoBro #MensHealth

We’re thankful for all of our Mo’s around the world (and for the delicious Thanksgiving leftovers in our moustache).
.
Happy Thanksgiving, folks!
.
.
#Movember #Moustache #Thanksgiving #Seinfeld

“I’m the oldest in our family, and then I have my sister, and then Andy is our baby brother. He was 7 years younger than me. And he was larger than life. He was funny, he was caring, he was the one that would say what everyone was thinking but no-one was brave enough to say. He’s really missed. He was the joy in our lives, and he was the one that brought everyone together. It’s so hard to fathom that he’s no longer here with us. I know my world will never be the same now that Andy has left.

If there are other families out there that don’t need to experience the loss of a loved one and other individuals that can seek help before making the same choices Andy did, then the world is going to be better off, because no place is better off for losing our men to suicide.” - Katie Bourke (Melbourne)
.
.
#Movember #MensHeath #WhyIMo #InTheBarberChair

Just a Mountie Mo Bro and his Dogstable Abbey.
.
.
#Movember #Mountie #WhyIMo #MensHealth

One of London’s longest standing murals ‘SCARY’ has been revived for Movember.
.
Artist Ben Eine has printed 60 Movember Mo’s as a wallpaper behind the lettering, representing the number of men who die by suicide every hour, globally.
.
“Mental health issues are nearly always misunderstood or overlooked. Art has the power to shine a light on this and trigger positivity and hope where it's really needed. Reviving 'SCARY' in such an iconic location for Movember will do just that." - Ben Eine
.
Eine is releasing a limited edition print of the work to raise funds for Movember. Get your hands on one of the 100 prints from ourtypes.com.
.
.
#Movember #MensHealth #Moustache #Graffiti #BenEine #MentalHealthAwareness

We're into the home stretch. You might have been a little unsure of your Mo at first, but no doubt it's grown on you.

Now's the time to chase those donations pledged to you on Mo 1. And if you need a reminder what we stand for, and why we Mo - take a listen to the following film from a few familiar faces.
.
.
#Movember #MensHealth #Moustache #WhyIMo

"When your friend asks you to help him win a calendar photo competition." - Joe Casson

Joe made the right decision here. A Mo Bro always has your back, and should have great costume instincts.
.
.
#Movember #MoBro #Moustache #freddiemercury

“I don’t feel like any less of a man because I have one testicle. And because I did go see the doctor when I did and did catch it early, my outcome was eventually going to be ok.” - @nathangadrian .
.
In December of 2018, life couldn’t have been better for Olympic swimmer Nathan Adrian. He had just gotten married and was training to make the Olympic swimming team for Tokyo 2020. Then, came something Nathan didn’t plan for. He noticed swelling in one of his testicles and decided to go get it checked out. The next thing Nathan knew, he was being tested and diagnosed with testicular cancer.
.
.
Less than a year and two surgeries later, Nathan is back in the pool training for Tokyo 2020 because of early detection. To watch Nathan’s full story check out the link in profile.
.
.
#Movember #WhyIMo #Tokyo2020 #USASwimming #OlympicSwimming

This weekend saw the 14th annual 70’s surfing competition, The Morning Of The Mo, take place. Few things are more Movember than this event.
.
“The Morning Of The Mo surf contest celebrates a time when shorts where tight, Mo’s were thick, and the surfing was smooth.”
.
.
#Movember #MensHealth #Moustache #Surf #MorningOfTheMo
For those who’ve been putting up with a Mo this month. Make the pash rash worth it. Donate Now. Link in bio.

"Our shop is named Mildred, after my grandmother who was the rock in my family. My mom had me at 17 and my biological father was not part of my life for quite some time, so needless to say we had some difficult times. I was lucky to have so many friends that supported me and accepted me even though I lived in the wrong part of town and we didn’t have much. I met my dad at 17, who is a barber and the reason I am today. I appreciate my modest upbringing because it has allowed me to to truly appreciate circumstance and be more empathetic." - Rob McMillen (NYC)

Rob is co-founder of Mildred New York and a L'Oréal Men Expert Barber.
.
.
#Movember #InTheBarberChair #WhyIMo #menshealth
Moustaches, at ease. It’s Sunday. Time to chill.

Flannel shirts and moustaches. It's a tried and tested union. And not, as some may think, reserved exclusively for the hipster.
.
This week saw the biggest gathering of plaid clad Mo’s for the 3rd edition of the Flanno 5k in Australia.
.
Hosting an event is all about having a good time, starting conversations, and raising funds. How are you Hosting for the final week of Movember?
.
.
#Movember #Host #Move #MensHealth

Your Mo helps fund programs like this Making Connections project: Kalihi Valley Instructional Bike Exchange (KVIBE).
.
Fresh air, flowing streams, and lush green mountains embrace the generous people of Kalihi Valley. In contrast, poverty, loss of cultural identity, and low-educational attainment have put men and boys living in Kalihi Valley at risk of depression, stress, and other mental health challenges.
.
KVIBE engages boys and young men in activities that provide safe spaces for them to be physically active, develop their bike mechanical skills, and grow as community leaders.
.
“KVIBE is not just a bike shop but a place of healing for men."
.
Visit link in bio to watch full film.
.
.
#Movember #MensHealth #MentalHealthAwareness #WhyIMo

You’ve been staring. It’s time to let him know. That’s one great Mo.
.
.
#movember #moustache #mo #fridayfeels

All week our friends at TikTok have been asking their community to get creative with #Movember challenge.

Guinness World Records got involved and reminded us about this beauty. The world’s longest moustache is believed to be a 14ft monster belonging to Ram Singh Chauhan of Rajastan, India, who regularly massages it with mustard and coconut oil to keep it healthy.
.
.
#Movember #Moustache #MoBro #GuinnessWorldRecord

"I jumped on a boat one day, going over to an island just off the coast of Australia. A good mate sat beside me and started talking, and he said “I went through this as well.” We’ve been mates for a long time, I didn’t even know he had prostate cancer. Guys feel shame that they’ve got this, and they don’t wanna tell anyone about it because they want to own it themselves.

I now get calls from guys who have been told they’ve got prostate cancer. They’ve been watching what I’ve been talking about. And listening. One got checked and said “what can you tell me about it?” - Charles Jia (Australia)

Hear more from Charles on IGTV.
.
.
#Movember #MensHealth #ProstateCancer #WhyIMo #InTheBarberChair
